doc.previous: Since unlike a jet engine a conventional rocket motor lacks an air intake there is no ram drag to deduct from the gross thrust Consequently the net thrust of a rocket motor is equal to the gross thrust apart from static back pressure
doc.after: Maximum efficiency for a rocket engine is achieved by maximising the momentum contribution of the equation without incurring penalties from over expanding the exhaust This occurs when Since ambient pressure changes with altitude most rocket engines spend very little time operating at peak efficiency
